cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and speech analysis to predict ratings of TED Talks. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper uses audio features to predict the ratings. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes three neural network architectures and compares with statistical machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses machine learning techniques to predict the ratings. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a possible category as the paper deals with analyzing ratings from spontaneous visitors of the website.
